ne disaster]] (Turkey, 3 days; [[Northern Cyprus]], 2 days; Pakistan, 1 day)<ref>{{cite news|title=National mourning declared in Turkey|url=http://news.az/articles/turkey/88355|accessdate=20 May 2014|newspaper=News.Az|date=14 May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://pmo.gov.pk/press_release_detailes.php?pr_id=491|title= Pakistan to observe day of mourning solidarity with Turkey|publisher=Prime Ministry of Pakistan|date=2014-05-14|accessdate=2014-05-14}}</ref>\n*Victims of the [[2014 Southeast Europe floods]] ([[Serbia]], 3 days; [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]], 1 day)<ref>{{cite news|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/2014/05/20/uk-balkans-flood-idUKKBN0E00Z620140520|title=Serbia declares national mourning, flood toll rises|agency=Reuters|date=2014-05-20|accessdate=2014-05-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.independent.mk/article_print.php?id=5197&show_logo=true|title=Day of Mourning Today in Bosnia and Herzegovina and Serb Republic|publisher=independent.mk|date=2014-05-20|accessdate=2014-05-20}}</ref>\n*Victims of [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic in mainland China|COVID-19]], ([[China]], April 4, 2020, 1 day)<ref>{{cite web |title=\u56fd\u52a1\u9662\u53d1\u5e03\u516c\u544a\uff1a2020\u5e744\u67084\u65e5\u4e3e\u884c\u5168\u56fd\u6027\u54c0\u60bc\u6d3b\u52a8 |url=https://www.sohu.com/a/385241304_428290?_trans_=000014_bdss_dkqgadr |website=[[Sohu]] |publisher=[[China Central Television]] |accessdate=2020-04-04 |language=zh |date=2020-04-03}}</ref> \n[[File:Fallen 44 PNP SAF.jpg|200px|thumb|right|The 44 police officers who perished during the [[Mamasapano clash]]]]\n\n==1800-1899==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"  style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n! Country\n! Year\n! Days of mourning\n! Reason\n! Notes\n|-\n| {{flag|United States}}\n| 1865\n| 1\n| [[Assassination of Abraham Lincoln|Assassination]] of U.S. President [[Abraham Lincoln]]\n| A National Day of Mourning was held on June 1.<ref>{{cite web |author=The President of the United States of America |title=The Obsequies; President Lincoln's Murder Planned in Canada. One of the Seward Assassins a St. Albans Robber. OFFICIAL DAY OF MOURNING APPOINTED. Progress of the Funeral Cortege from Philadelphia. Demonstrations of the People of New-Jersey. Reception of the Remains in this City...|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1865/04/25/archives/the-obsequies-president-lincolns-murder-planned-in-canada-one-of.html |website=The New York Times |date=April 25, 1865}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=National Day of Mourning, June 1st, 1865. Abraham Lincoln, Died April 15, 1865. |url=https://www.loc.gov/resource/lprbscsm.scsm0575/ |website=Library of Congress}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Netherlands}}\n| 1890\n| 1\n| Death of King [[William III of the Netherlands|William III]]\n| <ref>{{cite web |title=Dag van nationale rouw in de Nederlandse geschiedenis |url=https://isgeschiedenis.nl/nieuws/dag-van-nationale-rouw-in-de-nederlandse-geschiedenis |website=IsGeschiedenis |language=nl |date=March 16, 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|United States}}\n| 1881\n| 1\n| Death of U.S. President [[James A. Garfield]]\n| <ref>{{cite web |author1=The President of the United States of America |title=Proclamation 250\u2014Day of Mourning for James A. Garfield |url=https://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/documents/proclamation-250-day-mourning-for-james-garfield |website=The American Presidency Project}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==1900s==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"  style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n! Country\n! Year\n! Days of mourning\n! Reason\n! Notes\n|- \n| {{flag|United Kingdom}}\n| 1901\n| 11\n| Death of [[Queen Victoria]]\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|United States}}\n| 1901\n| 1 \n| [[Assassination of William McKinley|Assassination]] of U.S. President [[William McKinley]]\n| <ref>{{cite web |author1=The President of the United States of America |title=Proclamation 465\u2014Announcing the Death of William McKinley |url=https://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/documents/proclamation-465-announcing-the-death-william-mckinley |website=The American Presidency Project