on/09/04/09/sept-7-21-declared-non-working-holidays |title=Sept 7, 21 declared non-working holidays |publisher=ABS-CBN News |date=2009-09-06 |accessdate=2016-07-15}}</ref>\n*[[Sister L\u00facia]], (Portugal)\n*[[Mother Teresa of Calcutta]], (mainly India, Albania, and some Roman Catholic countries)\n*[[Maxim of Bulgaria|Patriarch Maxim of Bulgaria]] ([[Bulgaria]])\n*[[Serbian Patriarch Pavle]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.b92.net/eng/news/politics-article.php?yyyy=2009&mm=11&dd=16&nav_id=63065 |title=Serbia observes first day of mourning |publisher=B92 |date=2009-11-16 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110608081557/http://www.b92.net/eng/news/politics-article.php?yyyy=2009&mm=11&dd=16&nav_id=63065 |archivedate=2011-06-08}}</ref>\n*[[Pope John Paul II]], (many countries including [[Egypt]], [[Hungary]], [[Cuba]] (three days), [[Italy]], [[Ireland]], [[Seychelles]], [[Malawi]], the [[Republic of the Congo]], the [[Democratic Republic of Congo]], [[Portugal]] (three days), [[Brazil]], [[Poland]] (seven days), [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]], [[Mexico]], [[Spain]], the [[Czech Republic]] and [[Slovenia]])<ref>{{cite news |last1=McFadden |first1=Robert D. |title=In Many Lands and Tongues, Remembering Pope as Minister of Peace |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2005/04/04/world/europe/in-many-lands-and-tongues-remembering-pope-as-minister-of.html |accessdate=9 January 2020 |work=[[The New York Times]] |date=4 April 2005}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=World Mourns Pope John Paul II - Novinite.com - Sofia News Agency |url=https://www.novinite.com/articles/46319/World+Mourns+Pope+John+Paul+II |accessdate=9 January 2020 |work=www.novinite.com |date=April 3, 2005}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=World mourns Pope John Paul II |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/7357164/ns/world_news-one_year_later_remembering_pope_john_paul_ii/t/world-mourns-pope-john-paul-ii/#.Xhc15Mg3mM8 |accessdate=9 January 2020 |publisher=[[MSNBC]] |date=18 April 2005 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Kole |first1=William J. |last2=Falconi |first2=Marta |title=Miles of mourners for the pope: 100,000 attend as John Paul's body is put on public display |url=http://archive.decaturdaily.com/decaturdaily/news/050405/pope.shtml |accessdate=9 January 2020 |work=Decatur Daily |agency=[[Associated Press]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Taoiseach declares period of 'official mourning' |url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/taoiseach-declares-period-of-official-mourning-1.1175640 |accessdate=9 January 2020 |work=[[The Irish Times]] |date=April 4, 2005 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Spolar |first1=Christine |title=Day of mourning for `great Pole' |url=https://www.chicagotribune.com/news/ct-xpm-2005-04-06-0504060238-story.html |accessdate=9 January 2020 |work=[[Chicago Tribune]] |date=April 6, 2005}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Donaghy |first1=Kathy |title=Grieving days across the world are different things to different peoples |url=https://www.independent.ie/world-news/grieving-days-across-the-world-are-different-things-to-different-peoples-25988241.html |accessdate=9 January 2020 |work=Independent.ie |date=April 5, 2005 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Walsh |first1=Sister Mary Ann |title=From Pope John Paul II to Benedict XVI: An Inside Look at the End of an Era, the Beginning of a New One, and the Future of the Church |date=2005 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |isbn=978-1-58051-202-2 |page=188 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_jqs9rD39ewC&pg=PA188&lpg=PA188&dq=pope+john+paul+ii+%22national+day+of+mourning%22&source=bl&ots=pdH4zR8Tg_&sig=ACfU3U0Qrjbw76VVS2dFTk1XAAcHdifzoQ&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjT46vK3PbmAhVDTd8KHWqBBCo4ChDoATAAegQICRAB#v=onepage&q=pope%20john%20paul%20ii%20%22national%20day%20of%20mourning%22&f=false |accessdate=9 January 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Spain a nation in mourning for Pope John Paul II |url=https://www.expatica.com/es/uncategorized/spain-a-nation-in-mourning-for-pope-john-paul-ii/ |accessdate=9 Ja