ic [[Jaroslav Kubera]]\n| <ref>[https://www.idnes.cz/zpravy/domaci/kubera-statni-smutek.A200127_102209_domaci_kop P\u0159\u00ed\u0161t\u00ed pond\u011bl\u00ed bude v \u010cesku st\u00e1tn\u00ed smutek k uct\u011bn\u00ed pam\u00e1tky sen\u00e1tora Kubery]</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Kenya}}\n| 2020\n| 9\n| Death of the former President of Kenya [[Daniel arap Moi]]\n| <ref>[https://www.scribd.com/document/445467076/PRESIDENTIAL-PROCLAMATION-With-Respect-To-THE-DEATH-OF-H-E-DANIEL-TOROITICH-arap-MOI-C-G-H PRESIDENTIAL PROCLAMATION - With Respect To - THE DEATH OF H.E. DANIEL TOROITICH arap MOI, C.G.H.]</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Egypt}}\n| 2020\n| 3\n| Death of former president of Egipt [[Hosni Mubarak]]\n| <ref>[https://www.egyptindependent.com/egyptian-presidency-announces-three-days-of-national-mourning-following-mubaraks-death/ Egyptian Presidency announces three days of national mourning following Mubarak\u2019s death]</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Italy}}\n| rowspan=2|2020\n| rowspan=2|1\n| Martyrs who died in the fight against the [[2019-20 coronavirus pandemic|novel coronavirus disease (COVID-19) outbreak]] and compatriots who died of the disease\n| <ref>[https://www.positanonews.it/2020/03/ravello-giornata-lutto-nazionale-martedi-31-marzo-2020-ore-12/3375250/]</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|China}}\n| <ref>[https://news.cgtn.com/news/2020-04-03/China-to-mourn-COVID-19-victims-on-April-4-PnBkfHYb2E/index.html China to mourn COVID-19 martyrs, victims nationwide on April 4]</ref>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[European Day of Mourning]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n[[Category:Death customs]]\n[[Category:National days]]\n", "name_user": "Wiktorantkowiak25", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200e2020s", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_day_of_mourning"}
{"title_page": "Opinion polling for the next United Kingdom general election", "text_new": "{|class=\"infobox\"\n|[[2015 United Kingdom general election|2015 general election]] '''\u2022''' [[Opinion polling for the 2015 United Kingdom general election|Opinion polls]]\n|-\n|[[2017 United Kingdom general election|2017 general election]] '''\u2022''' [[Opinion polling for the 2017 United Kingdom general election|Opinion polls]]\n|-\n|[[2019 United Kingdom general election|2019 general election]] '''\u2022''' [[Opinion polling for the 2019 United Kingdom general election|Opinion polls]]\n|-\n|[[Next United Kingdom general election|Next general election]] '''\u2022''' '''Opinion polls'''\n|}\nIn the run up to the [[next United Kingdom general election]], various organisations are expected to carry out [[opinion polling]] to gauge voting intention. Results of such polls are displayed in this article. Most of the polling companies listed are members of the [[British Polling Council]] (BPC) and abide by its disclosure rules.\n\nThe date range for these opinion polls is from the [[2019 United Kingdom general election|previous general election]], held on 12 December 2019, to the present day. Under current [[Fixed-term Parliaments Act 2011|fixed-term legislation]], the next general election is scheduled to be held in May 2024,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Tufft|first1=Ben|title=When will the next UK General Election be held?|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/generalelection/when-will-the-next-uk-general-election-be-held-10236102.html|newspaper=The Independent|accessdate=29 December 2019|quote=The act specifies that future elections will be held on the first Thursday of May, every five years.|date=8 May 2015}}</ref> though the government has pledged to repeal this law.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://blogs.spectator.co.uk/2019/12/full-transcript-the-queens-speech/|title=Full transcript: The Queen\u2019s Speech|date=19 December 2019|accessdate=30 January 2020|work=The Spectator}}</ref>\n\nMost opinion polls do not cover [[Northern Ireland]], since its major political parties are different to those in the rest of the United Kingdom.\n\n== Graphical summary ==\n{{Opinion polling for the next United Kingdom general election}}\n\n== National poll results==\nPoll results are listed in the table below in reverse chronological order. The highest percentage figure in each polling survey is displayed in bold, and the background shaded in the leading party's colour. The 'party lead' column shows the percentage-point difference between the two parties with the highest figures. In the instance of a tie, no figure is shaded but both are displayed in bold.\n\nThe parties with the largest numbers of votes in the 2019 general election are listed here. Other parties are listed in the \"Other\" column.\n\n=== 2020 ===\n{{for|events during the year|2020 in the United Kingdom}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:90%;line-height:14px;\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Pollster\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Client\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Dates<br>conducted\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Area\n! rowspan=\"2\" data-sort-type=\"number\" | Sample<br>size\n! class=\"unsortable\" style=\"width:50px;\" |[[Conservative Party (UK)|Con]]\n! class=\"unsortable\" style=\"width:50px;\" |[[Labour Party (UK)|Lab]]\n! class=\"unsortable\" style=\"width:50px;\" |[[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Lib Dem]]\n! class=\"unsortable\" style=\"width:50px;\" |[[Scottish National Party|SNP]]\n! class=\"unsortable\" style=\"width:50px;\"| [[Plaid Cymru]]\n! class=\"unsortable\" style=\"width:50px;\" |[[Green parties in the United Kingdom (disambiguation)|Green]]\n! class=\"unsortable\" style=\"width:50px;\" |[[Brexit Party|Brexit]]\n! rowspan=\"2\" class=\"unsortable\" | Other\n! rowspan=\"2\" data-sort-type=\"number\" | Lead\n|-\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" style=\"background:{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}};\" |\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" style=\"background:{{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color